text: Bietigheim-Bissingen (German pronunciation: [ˌbiːtikʰhaim ˈbisiŋən]) is a city in the northern centre of Baden-Württemberg in Germany, about north of Stuttgart and south of Heilbronn. It is the second biggest city in the district of Ludwigsburg; only Ludwigsburg City is bigger. == Twin towns == Bietigheim-Bissingen is twinned with: * Kusatsu, Japan, since 1962 * Sucy-en- Brie, France, since 1967 * Surrey Heath, United Kingdom, since 1971 * Szekszárd, Hungary, since 1989 * Overland Park, USA, since 1999 ==References== ==Other websites==
title: Bietigheim-Bissingen
